## Browser surfaces (Pack E)

If you give the Architect a browser agent (for example Claude in Chrome), it is read-only by convention per Layer 1 Rule 18: navigate, read, screenshot only; never a state-changing click, credential entry, OAuth or consent grant, or form submission. State-changing web actions route to the Operator or to the Executor via a CLI such as gh. List the specific pages this project's Architect may read so they are explicit.

{{BROWSER_SURFACES_OR_EMPTY}}

## Process watcher (Pack W)

A read-only process-watcher sensor may notify the Operator when Claude Code exits, so the Operator does not babysit the terminal. Contract: it triggers on Claude Code process exit (alive means silent, exited means notify) and branches on report freshness (a fresh step report present means ready for review, none means ended without report, check). It reads files and process state only; it never writes, never commits, and never emits the Operator's proceed signal. The sensor implementation is project-specific and machine-specific; record it here if this project uses one.

{{WATCHER_IMPLEMENTATION_OR_EMPTY}}

